  <span id="freeText15671505925609826300" style="display:none">Maureen Johnson's second novel, The Bermudez Triangle, was famously banned by a school library in Oklahoma. Why? Lesbian content. I know! In a young adult book! Whatever next? Is it shocking and likely to corrupt our teenagers? Is it heck!<br /><br />When Nina Bermudez goes attends a college study program during the summer, her best friends and the other two sides of the triangle (I wanted to say "titular triangle" there, but I thought, given the whole banning thing, I'd better not), Avery and Melanie don't know how they're going to manage without her. But before too long, they find that <br /><br />For the rest of this review, read<br /><a target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow" href="http://www.trashionista.com/2007/12/book-review-t-2.html">http://www.trashionista.com/2007/12/b...</a></span>
